    {"turn": 2, "polarity": "+", "annotation": "Move on the framing of the question itself rather than answering it — invites self-reflection without engaging the victim premise. Well-timed opener."},
    {"turn": 4, "polarity": "+", "annotation": "Mirrors client's 'detective work' language to maintain rapport, then surgically points at 'to me' and offers 'suspect' as an experiment. Refuses victim frame as invitation, not accusation. Exactly the right move for the read."}
